1 (d)[(b)] The Kentucky Community and Technical College System mandatory fee
2 established in this subsection shall only be used for debt service on agency
3 bond projects.
4 (e)[(c)] Any fee established as provided by this subsection shall cease to be
5 assessed upon the retirement of the project bonds for which it services debt.
6 (f)[(d)] Prior to the issuance of any bonds, the Kentucky Community and
7 Technical College System shall certify in writing to the secretary of the
8 Finance and Administration Cabinet that sufficient funds have been raised to
9 meet the local match equivalent to twenty-five percent (25%) of the total
10 project cost;
11 (9) Devise, establish, and periodically review and revise policies to be used in making
12 recommendations to the Governor for consideration in developing
13 recommendations to the General Assembly for appropriations to the universities,
14 the Kentucky Community and Technical College System, and to support strategies
15 for persons to maintain necessary levels of literacy throughout their lifetimes. The
16 council has sole discretion, with advice of the Strategic Committee on
17 Postsecondary Education and the executive officers of the postsecondary education
18 system, to devise policies that provide for allocation of funds among the
19 universities and the Kentucky Community and Technical College System;
20 (10) Lead and provide staff support for the biennial budget process as provided under
21 KRS Chapter 48, in cooperation with the committee;
22 (11) (a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, review and approve all
23 capital construction projects covered by KRS 45.750(1)(f), including real
24 property acquisitions, and regardless of the source of funding for projects or
25 acquisitions. Approval of capital projects and real property acquisitions shall
26 be on a basis consistent with the strategic agenda and the mission of the
27 respective universities and the Kentucky Community and Technical College
