UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1152
1 System.
2 (b) The organized groups that are establishing community college satellites as
3 branches of existing community colleges in the counties of Laurel, Leslie, and
4 Muhlenberg, and that have substantially obtained cash, pledges, real property,
5 or other commitments to build the satellite at no cost to the Commonwealth,
6 other than operating costs that shall be paid as part of the operating budget of
7 the main community college of which the satellite is a branch, are authorized
8 to begin construction of the satellite on or after January 1, 1998;
9 (12) Require reports from the executive officer of each institution it deems necessary for
10 the effectual performance of its duties;
11 (13) Ensure that the state postsecondary system does not unnecessarily duplicate
12 services and programs provided by private postsecondary institutions and shall
13 promote maximum cooperation between the state postsecondary system and private
14 postsecondary institutions. Receive and consider an annual report prepared by the
15 Association of Independent Kentucky Colleges and Universities stating the
16 condition of independent institutions, listing opportunities for more collaboration
17 between the state and independent institutions and other information as appropriate;
18 (14) Establish course credit, transfer, and degree components as required in KRS
19 164.2951;
20 (15) (a) Define and approve the offering of all postsecondary education technical,
21 associate, baccalaureate, graduate, and professional degree, certificate, or
22 diploma programs in the public postsecondary education institutions. The
23 council shall not approve a new degree, certificate, or diploma program that
24 includes a requirement for a course or training of which the primary purpose
25 is to indoctrinate participants with a discriminatory concept.
26 (b) The council shall expedite wherever possible the approval of requests from
27 the Kentucky Community and Technical College System board of regents
