UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1152
1 relating to new certificate, diploma, technical, or associate degree programs of
2 a vocational-technical and occupational nature. Without the consent of the
3 General Assembly, the council shall not abolish or limit the total enrollment
4 of the general program offered at any community college to meet the goal of
5 reasonable access throughout the Commonwealth to a two (2) year course of
6 general studies designed for transfer to a baccalaureate program. This does not
7 restrict or limit the authority of the council, as set forth in this section, to
8 eliminate or make changes in individual programs within that general
9 program;
10 (16) Eliminate, in its discretion, existing programs or make any changes in existing
11 academic programs at the state's postsecondary educational institutions, taking into
12 consideration these criteria:
13 (a) Consistency with the institution's mission and the strategic agenda;
14 (b) Alignment with the priorities in the strategic implementation plan for
15 achieving the strategic agenda;
16 (c) Elimination of unnecessary duplication of programs within and among
17 institutions;
18 (d) Efforts to create cooperative programs with other institutions through
19 traditional means, or by use of distance learning technology and electronic
20 resources, to achieve effective and efficient program delivery; and
21 (e) Alignment with KRS 164.2895, including the elimination of any program that
22 includes a requirement for a course or training of which the primary purpose
23 is to indoctrinate participants with a discriminatory concept;
24 (17) Ensure the governing board and faculty of all postsecondary education institutions
25 are committed to providing instruction free of discrimination against students who
26 hold political views and opinions contrary to those of the governing board and
27 faculty;
