BR115200.100 - 1152 - XXXX 1/29/2026 8:09 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1152
1 Community and Technical College System a comprehensive orientation and
2 education program for new members of the council and the governing boards
3 and continuing education opportunities for all council and board members.
4 For new members of the council and institutional governing boards, the
5 council shall:
6 1. Ensure that the orientation and education program comprises six (6)
7 hours of instruction time and includes but is not limited to information
8 concerning the roles of the council and governing board members, the
9 strategic agenda and the strategic implementation plan, and the
10 respective institution's mission, budget and finances, strategic plans and
11 priorities, institutional policies and procedures, board fiduciary
12 responsibilities, legal considerations including open records and open
13 meetings requirements, ethical considerations arising from board
14 membership, and the board member removal and replacement
15 provisions of KRS 63.080;
16 2. Establish delivery methods by which the orientation and education
17 program can be completed in person or electronically by new members
18 within one (1) year of their appointment or election;
19 3. Provide an annual report to the Governor and Legislative Research
20 Commission of those new board members who do not complete the
21 required orientation and education program; and
22 4. Invite governing board members of private colleges and universities
23 licensed by the Council on Postsecondary Education to participate in the
24 orientation and education program described in this subsection;
25 (b) Offer, in cooperation with the public universities and the Kentucky
26 Community and Technical College System, continuing education
27 opportunities for all council and governing board members; and
