1 (c) Review and approve the orientation programs of each public university and
2 the Kentucky Community and Technical College System for their governing
3 board members to ensure that all programs and information adhere to this
4 subsection;
5 (25) Develop a financial reporting procedure to be used by all state postsecondary
6 education institutions to ensure uniformity of financial information available to
7 state agencies and the public;
8 (26) Select and appoint a president of the council under KRS 164.013;
9 (27) Employ consultants and other persons and employees as may be required for the
10 council's operations, functions, and responsibilities;
11 (28) Promulgate administrative regulations, in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A,
12 governing its powers, duties, and responsibilities as described in this section;
13 (29) Prepare and present by January 31 of each year an annual status report on
14 postsecondary education in the Commonwealth to the Governor, the Strategic
15 Committee on Postsecondary Education, and the Legislative Research Commission;
16 (30) Consider the role, function, and capacity of independent institutions of
17 postsecondary education in developing policies to meet the immediate and future
18 needs of the state. When it is found that independent institutions can meet state
19 needs effectively, state resources may be used to contract with or otherwise assist
20 independent institutions in meeting these needs;
21 (31) Create advisory groups representing the presidents, faculty, nonteaching staff, and
22 students of the public postsecondary education system and the independent colleges
23 and universities;
24 (32) Develop a statewide policy to promote employee and faculty development in state
25 and locally operated secondary area technology centers through the waiver of
26 tuition for college credit coursework in the public postsecondary education system.
27 Any regular full-time employee of a state or locally operated secondary area
Page 8 of 10
BR115200.100 - 1152 - XXXX 1/29/2026 8:09 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1152
1 technology center may, with prior administrative approval of the course offering
2 institution, take a maximum of six (6) credit hours per term at any public
3 postsecondary institution. The institution shall waive the tuition up to a maximum
4 of six (6) credit hours per term. The employee shall complete the Free Application
5 for Federal Student Aid to determine the level of need and eligibility for state and
6 federal financial aid programs. The amount of tuition waived shall not exceed the
7 cost of tuition at the institution less any state or federal grants received, which shall
8 be credited first to the student's tuition;
9 (33) Participate with the Kentucky Department of Education, the Kentucky Board of
10 Education, and postsecondary education institutions to ensure that academic content
11 requirements for successful entry into postsecondary education programs are
12 aligned with high school content standards and that students who master the high
13 school academic content standards shall not need remedial courses. The council
14 shall monitor the results on an ongoing basis;
15 (34) Cooperate with the Kentucky Department of Education and the Education
16 Professional Standards Board in providing information sessions to selected
17 postsecondary education content faculty and teacher educators of the high school
18 academic content standards as required under KRS 158.6453(2)(l);
19 (35) Cooperate with the Office of the Kentucky Center for Statistics and ensure the
20 participation of the public institutions as required in KRS 151B.133;
21 (36) Pursuant to KRS 63.080, review written notices from the Governor or from a board
22 of trustees or board of regents concerning removal of a board member or the entire
23 appointed membership of a board, investigate the member or board and the conduct
24 alleged to support removal, and make written recommendations to the Governor
25 and the Legislative Research Commission as to whether the member or board
26 should be removed; and
27 (37) Exercise any other powers, duties, and responsibilities necessary to carry out the
